./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0043_1777735742.log:4571:sdp/logs/Verify_T-026_20260416T181925Z_1776399739.log:143:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:22:58.893Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776399778893_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-026@20260416t181925z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-026@20260416T181925Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-17\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/groove_engine.py`\n- `tests/test_groove_engine.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of the tempo-dependent swing curve accurately follows the Friberg & Sundström (2002) model. \n- The swing ratio is dynamically computed based on the current tempo when `tempo_dependent_swing=True`.\n- The short-note duration is successfully held near 100 ms across the tempo range (as verified by `TestFribergShortNoteInvariance`).\n- Role-specific overrides for `ride`/`cymbal` (wider ratio) and `benadon` (clamped to 1.2–1.7) are correctly implemented in `tempo_swing_ratio`.\n\n## Completeness\nAll acceptance criteria have been met:\n- [x] Swing ratio computed from current tempo.\n- [x] Short-note duration held near 100 ms.\n- [x] Optional role-specific overrides (ride, benadon).\n- [x] Tests verify ratio curve and short-note invariance.\n\n## Consistency\nThe changes follow the established patterns in `groove_engine.py`. The addition of `tempo_dependent_swing` to `GrooveProfile` and the update to `apply_groove_to_ioi` are consistent with how other groove parameters are handled. Metadata reporting in `groove_metadata_for_step` also correctly includes the new swing information.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues were identified. The implementation consists of pure mathematical transformations and metadata reporting.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured and documented. The test suite is comprehensive, covering edge cases like zero tempo, very fast tempi (where it returns to straight 1:1), and role-specific clamping.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is excellent and handles the non-linear relationship between tempo and swing ratio precisely as specified. Pre-existing startup hardening items (`bootstrap_identity`) were confirmed to be already addressed in the daemon entry points or otherwise out of scope for this pure-function logic task.\n"}}
