CHANGELOG.md:903:- Added depth-2 acoustic ecology end-to-end test coverage (frac-0056): `tests/test_acoustic_ecology.py` now includes `TestAcousticEcologyEndToEnd`, which drives the existing SenseWeave acoustic ecology resolver through daily context scenarios, mode-priority resolution, hard-ceiling tables, source ordering, policy range invariants, dwell-time/room-activity/day-phase modifier sweeps, conservative presence handling, performance override behavior, silence-window ordering, and reason metadata checks. `tests/test_acoustic_ecology_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2; the source resolver remains unchanged and existing startup identity anchors plus full validation remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:905:- Added depth-2 end-to-end accompaniment test coverage (frac-0055): `tests/test_accompaniment.py` now ships a new `TestAccompanimentEndToEnd` class that drives the existing Korsakov accompaniment public surface (`DensityTracker`, `select_accompaniment_type`, `breathing_swell`, `should_transition_gradually`, `should_pedal`, `pedal_note`, `get_pattern`, and the six pattern generators) through end-to-end multi-step pytest methods. The new tests sweep the documented density bands and verify the inverse-density rule, iterate every pattern type 1-6 to assert non-empty events with positive amps/releases, sweep `breathing_swell` over rest/active/edge inputs, walk full phrase boundaries through `should_pedal` + `pedal_note`, run the dense-melody and resting-melody pipelines end-to-end through a synthetic `DensityTracker` window, and pin a six-bar composer loop. A `test_test_accompaniment_reaches_depth_two` gate test asserts the file's fractal classification is at least depth 2. Existing `TestDensityTracker`, `TestSelectAccompanimentType`, `TestPatterns`, `TestPedalPoint`, `TestBreathing`, and `TestTransition` assertions are preserved unchanged; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py`, `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:907:- Added depth-2 pytest collection gate reports (frac-0054): `tests/conftest.py` now exposes a frozen `CollectionGateDecision` dataclass plus `collection_gate_decisions`, `apply_collection_gate_decisions`, and `summarize_collection_gate_decisions` so tests and diagnostics can inspect live/host-specific marker gates with enabled state, skip reason, matched count, skipped count, and JSON-safe totals. Existing `--run-live-modal`, `--run-live-replicate`, `live_modal`, `live_replicate`, and `cypherclaw_e2e` behavior is preserved: Modal/Replicate live tests skip by default unless opted in, and CypherClaw e2e skips on CI. `tests/test_conftest_depth.py` pins hook registration, default and CI gate behavior, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:909:- Added depth-2 test_genai smoke probe (frac-0053): root-level `test_genai.py` is now a typed module exposing a frozen `GenAIProbeResult` dataclass plus `create_genai_client`, `list_model_names`, `probe_genai_client`, `summarize_probe_result`, `format_probe_lines`, and `main` so callers, tests, and operator dashboards can drive `probe → summarize → render → main` without re-implementing the conditional script logic. The success path returns a populated result with the sampled model names; any raised `Exception` is folded into an `ok=False` result with the stringified error and zero models. `summarize_probe_result` is JSON-safe (`sampled_models` rendered as a list); `format_probe_lines` preserves the original CLI output format byte-for-byte ("Successfully created client without explicit API key." header plus per-model lines on success, single "Error: <error>" line on failure); `main()` runs the probe and prints each line, returning exit code 0 to match the original `python test_genai.py` smoke behavior. `tests/test_test_genai_depth.py` pins the new probe surface, client construction (explicit key + default-auth env), limit-respecting model sampling, success/error result paths, JSON-safe summary, canonical CLI line rendering, end-to-end main, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` and the startup identity anchors remain green.
