ist(...)` produces a single line for one item and a `- `-prefixed bulleted list for multiple items); the captured `output_func` blocks include the `"Startup Wizard"` banner and the `"Ready"` summary card; and a primitive diagnostic of the roster, applied config description and routing flags, per-agent capabilities and instruction files, the relative-path file list, and a focused-helper map round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_wizard_depth.py` pins the base test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method plus a machine-readable depth marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `promptclaw/wizard.py` already produced the required lifecycle output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4685 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
