CHANGELOG.md:938:- Added depth-2 composer quote verification reports (frac-0045): `my-claw/tools/composer_quote_verify.py` now exposes a frozen `QuoteVerificationReport` plus typed helpers `build_quote_verification_report`, `summarize_quote_verification_report`, `render_quote_verification_lines`, and `quote_verification_exit_code` around the existing hardware-free known-room/self-quote smoke path. The report captures descriptor identity/tags, requested/captured piece counts, song ids, match details, overlap, score, and status while preserving `trigger_composer_pieces`, `find_motif_tag_match`, and the CLI's existing success/failure output and exit codes. `tests/test_composer_quote_verify_depth.py` pins the end-to-end report, JSON-safe summary, CLI line rendering, failure-status exit mapping, and fractal depth >= 2; original composer quote, sample capture, self-listener, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:942:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifact run reports (frac-0043): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes frozen `ArtifactFileStatus` and `ArtifactRunReport` dataclasses plus `ArtifactManager.build_run_report()` so callers can summarize expected run files, present/missing counts, missing file names, event count, and latest event type from the canonical `ProjectPaths.run_layout()` and existing event log. Existing artifact write helpers, `read_events()`, JSONL event shape, and on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` filenames are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_report.py` pins written-artifact summaries, JSON-safe report output, and fractal depth >= 2; existing artifact depth tests and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:946:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw path layouts (frac-0041): `promptclaw/paths.py` now exposes a frozen `RunPathLayout` plus `ProjectPaths.run_layout()`, `ProjectPaths.ensure_run_layout()`, and `ProjectPaths.path_summary()` so project/run filesystem contracts can produce typed layouts, idempotently prepare run directories, and emit JSON-safe operator summaries. Existing project-level path attributes and `run_*` helper return values are preserved; `ArtifactManager.create_run_layout()` now iterates the canonical run layout while keeping the same on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` structure. Empty run ids fail fast with `ValueError` before layout creation. `tests/test_promptclaw_paths_depth.py` pins helper compatibility, JSON-safe summaries, layout preparation through `ArtifactManager`, run-id rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; config, orchestrator, artifact, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
